HEADWORD: Reformado
<hw>Ref`or*ma"do</hw> <pr>(-m?"d?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., fr.
<ets>reformar</ets>, L. <ets>reformare</ets>. SEe <er>Reform</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A monk of a reformed
order.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Weever.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An officer who, in disgrace, is deprived of his
command, but retains his rank, and sometimes his pay.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reformalize</ent>⟦br⟧
